1 2. “Harmful woody species” means a tree or shrub species that
2 is rapidly encroaching into adjoining lands and is likely to cause
3 harm to the environment or economy. Harmful woody species include,
4 but are not limited to, Juniperus virginiana (Eastern Redcedar),
5 Juniperus scopulorum (Rocky Mountain juniper), Juniperus monosperma
6 (oneseed juniper) and, Tamarix ramosissima (salt cedar), Juniperus
7 pinchotii (redberry juniper), Juniper ashei (ashe juniper), and
8 Prosopis glandulosa (honey mesquite); and
9 3. “North Canadian Watershed” means the an area of land in
10 Oklahoma that drains or sheds water into the North Canadian River a
11 waterway or water basin.
12 B. There Subject to the availability of funds, there is hereby
13 created a statewide pilot program to remove or eradicate harmful
14 woody species in the North Canadian Watershed watersheds to be
15 administered by through the Oklahoma Conservation Commission. To
16 accomplish the goals listed in this section, the Commission is
17 authorized to use the funds available in the North Canadian
18 Watershed Water Restoration Revolving Fund established in Section 3
19 of this act 3-8-103 of this title. The purpose of the program is to
20 manage and eradicate, where possible, harmful woody species that
21 damage grazing lands, create significant wildfire risk, reduce
22 wildlife habitat and reduce water flow into the North Canadian River
23 waterways and water basins.
24 C. In administering the pilot program, the Commission shall:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB263 SFLR Page 2
