1 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY Section 3, Chapter 372, O.S.L.
2 2023 (27A O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 3-8-103), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 3-8-103. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
5 a revolving fund for the Oklahoma Conservation Commission to be
6 designated the “North Canadian Watershed Water Restoration Revolving
7 Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
8 year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
9 Conservation Commission from appropriations, federal grants or
10 funds, municipal contributions, private contributions, and any other
11 sources, including interest earned from the income in the fund, that
12 are designated for deposit to such fund or designated for duties
13 associated with harmful woody species removal from the North
14 Canadian Watershed watersheds throughout the state. All monies
15 accruing to the credit of said the fund are hereby appropriated and
16 may be budgeted and expended by the Conservation Commission to
17 perform the duties imposed on the Commission by law. Expenditures
18 from said the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State
19 Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
20 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
21 approval and payment.
22 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
